{
  "texts": [
    "It aims at the two major problems of how to model and how to analyze in numerical experimental research.",
    "It no longer relies on the continuity assumption and near equilibrium approximation of traditional fluid modeling, and it abandons the \"lattice gas\" images of standard LBM.",
    "It adds detection, presentation, description, and analysis solutions based on phase space for discrete/TNE states and effects.",
    "Over time and according to the research needs, more information extraction techniques and complex physical field analysis schemes will be introduced.f (0)Although the flow behavior targeted is complex, the DBM approach is inherently simple.",
    "As far as the modeling method is concerned, it only needs to check the kinetic moments of involved in the more accurate constitutive relationships according to the orders of tensors, and determine them as the kinetic moments that needs to preserve value, instead of deriving extremely complex extended hydrodynamic equations like the KMM approach."
  ]
}